Labour minister Thulas Nxesi says the national minimum wage is now R21.69 for each ordinary hour. The new figures were published published last night. The change will take effect from 1 March 2021. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Farmers say they could let farmworkers go as a result of the new minimum wage. Labour minister Thulas Nxesi has raised farm and domestic workers' wages by double-digit figures.
The national minimum wage was first introduced in January 2019 at R20 an hour. READ: COVID-19 crisis affects lower-paid workers severely: ILO It will rise to R21.69 on the first of next month, an increase of 4.5 percent. Farmworkers currently earn at least R18.68 an hour while domestic workers now earn a minimum of R15.57 an hour. The Labour Department has recommended that domestic workers be aligned with the minimum wage by next year.